# ── Source / build-tag priorities ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Packages built from sources that are NOT binary repositories (SlackBuilds.org,
# your own local builds) carry a build tag after the build number, e.g.
# 1_SBo -> _SBo, 1_rtz -> _rtz. Give those tags a priority here, in the same
# scale as the repos above, so upgrade-all treats them as a prioritised source:
# a tagged package is only replaced by a candidate from a repo of HIGHER or
# EQUAL priority. With SBo at 100 below, your SBo packages are never silently
# migrated to conraid/alienbob etc... or downgraded; upgrade them via sbopkg/sbotools/slpkg etc.
# Format:  priority  name   tag
100        SBo    _SBo
100        local  _rtz
100        forge  _FRG
100        custom _custom
100        scmd   _SC
